               <head>Bi sarnamah</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Bī sarnāmah by ʻAṭṭār, Farīd al-Dīn, d. ca. 1230</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089787 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15659-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_120724759">ʻAṭṭār, Farīd al-Dīn, d. ca. 1230</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_120724759" type="supplied">عطار، فريد الدين</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6497">Bī sarnāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_6497">بی سرنامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A mystical mas̲navī poem almost certainly falsely attributed to Farīd al-Dīn ‘Aṭṭār (d. ca. 617/1220). </p>
                        <p>Other contents: numerous corrections in margins; inside front and back covers, miscellaneous scribbles; f. 1r, inscription Vuṣlat (a word that occurs in many bayts of the exordium of Bī sarnāmah).</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per" otherLangs="">Persian</textLang>
